# Compiler-tree changes

- These files are compiled by the committed seed binary `./w` on every
  `./wbuild build`. They must not use language syntax newer than the seed;
  new syntax is only usable here after a seed update via `./wbuild update`.
- Grammar/codegen modules do not compile standalone — diagnose them
  through the entry point: `./bin/wv2 check --json w.w`. (The edit hook
  does this mapping automatically.)
- Gate every change on `./wbuild verify` (self-host fixpoint, wv3 == wv4 ==
  wv5) and `./wbuild self_host_warning_test` (the compiler sources must stay
  warning-free). Run `./wbuild verify_x64` when codegen or word-size behavior
  is involved. `./bin/wtest changed <file>` prints exactly this set.
- Human-readable diagnostic text is frozen by `warning_test` and the
  `type_system_*_test` targets — never reword existing messages without
  updating those fixtures deliberately.
- New language syntax must also be added to the parser-generator grammar
  `tests/parser_generator/w.pg`; `parser_generator_w_test` parses every
  tracked `.w` file and fails on syntax it does not know.
- Run the full `./wbuild tests` before considering the
  change done.
